  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nRelated to #4675, the RPC tests in `lighthouse_network` will need to dial on the multiaddress received from libp2p as we want them to **not** assume which port to use (in order to improve CI stability to avoid racing on port numbers).\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently, port numbers are computed using our own handrolled implementation:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/2841f60686d642fcc0785c884d43e34e47a800dc/beacon_node/lighthouse_network/tests/common.rs#L99-L100\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nDon't assume which port we're listening on when constructing peers for testing purposes. Instead, only dial on multiaddress(es) returned by libp2p (which will handle port allocation for us by deferring to the kernel in the usual way).",
